    <title>string-width</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><anchor id="md_backend_2node__modules_2string-width_2readme_1autotoc_md3751"/> <blockquote><para><zwj/>Get the visual width of a string - the number of columns required to display it </para>
</blockquote></para>
<para>Some Unicode characters are <ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halfwidth_and_fullwidth_forms">fullwidth</ulink> and use double the normal width. <ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code">ANSI escape codes</ulink> are stripped and doesn&apos;t affect the width.</para>
<para>Useful to be able to measure the actual width of command-line output.</para>
<sect1 id="md_backend_2node__modules_2string-width_2readme_1autotoc_md3752">
<title>Install</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">$<sp/>npm<sp/>install<sp/>string-width</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md_backend_2node__modules_2string-width_2readme_1autotoc_md3753">
<title>Usage</title><para><programlisting filename=".js"><codeline><highlight class="normal">const<sp/>stringWidth<sp/>=<sp/>require(&apos;string-width&apos;);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">stringWidth(&apos;a&apos;);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">//=&gt;<sp/>1</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">stringWidth(&apos;古&apos;);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">//=&gt;<sp/>2</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">stringWidth(&apos;\u001B[1m古\u001B[22m&apos;);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">//=&gt;<sp/>2</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect1>
